landingRules:[
  "O&G/spill traffic NEVER lands on generic biochar education — it lands on absorbent/remediation value + a free-sample CTA (LOI as the follow-on step).",
  "Ag buyers NEVER see oilfield messaging — separate /agriculture track.",
  "NO bulk-quote or 'buy in bulk now' CTAs anywhere in Month 1 — the primary action is a free sample; the conversion is a signed LOI for Q4 supply.",
  "Every campaign has ONE specific primary CTA (free sample, spec, or intro) — never 'Learn More' or 'Get a bulk quote' as the primary action.",
  "Bedding page uses claim-controlled language only (absorbent/moisture; no animal-health claims).",
  "Products beyond Pellets + Biochar show as 'Coming Q4' — request-a-sample allowed but set the ~30-day lead-time expectation."
],

